Class MissingDefaultConstructorException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable

        • java.lang.RuntimeException

              • org.toolboxframework.scan.MissingDefaultConstructorException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MissingDefaultConstructorException
extends ToolScannerException
    This exception is raised if a class annotated with Tool or ToolMaker does not have a default constructor.

    This exception is a RuntimeException because it is exposed to the client. Using a RuntimeException avoids bad coding practices on the client side where they catch the exception and do nothing.
